  <description type="morphology">Leaf blades mostly 2.5–5 cm, margins pinnately toothed to pinnatifid. Involucres 6–8 m. Phyllary apices usually rounded, sometimes with weakly developed aristae. Florets 12–20. 2n = 12.</description>
  <description type="phenology">Flowering (May–)Aug–Nov.</description>
  <description type="habitat">Sandy soils, alkaline or salt flats, desert dunes, often with Saguaro-Prosopis-Larrea, Larrea, Atriplex, Yucca, or mixed shrubs;</description>
  <description type="elevation">(-15–)0–900(–1100) m;</description>
  <description type="distribution">Ariz., Calif., Nev., Utah; Mexico (Baja California, Sonora).</description>
  <number>1c.</number>
  <discussion>For the most part, var. eremophila is geographically separate from var. acradenia. In southwestern Nevada many intergrades occur; in San Bernadino County, California, the two taxa appear to be contiguous with little or no intergradation. In the latter area, the taxa apparently are at different ploidy levels.</discussion>
